/* Database structure: ["Nuclide_ID", [Z, N, Name, LevelEnergies, Halflives, HalflifeUnits, 
                                       DecayModes, BranchingRatios]]
   
   Field descriptions:
   - Nuclide_ID: String identifier (e.g., "185Tl")
   - Z: Atomic number (protons)
   - N: Neutron number
   - Name: Element symbol + mass number (e.g., "185Tl")
   - LevelEnergies: Array of excited state energies in MeV [0, 0.455, ...] (0 for ground state)
   - Halflives: Array of half-life values [19.5, 1.8, ...]
   - HalflifeUnits: Array of units ["s", "s", ...] (s, ms, us, ns, ps, fs, m, h, d, y, keV, MeV, eV)
   - DecayModes: Nested array [[mode1, mode2], [mode1]] for each level
   - BranchingRatios: Nested array [[ratio1, ratio2], [ratio1]] matching DecayModes (percentages)
   
   Note: null indicates missing or not applicable data
   Multiple excited states are combined in arrays for the same isotope
   Example: ["185Tl", [81, 104, "185Tl", [0, 0.455], [19.5, 1.8], ["s", "s"], 
                       [["EC+B+"], ["IT"]], [[100], [100]]]]
*/

